HEADWORD: Rufiopin
<hw>Ru`fi*o"pin</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>rufus</ets> reddish + <ets>op</ets>ianic.]</ety> <fld>(Chem.)</fld>
<def>A yellowish red crystalline substance related to anthracene, and
obtained from opianic acid.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

